column6: THOROUGHLY REASEARCHED AND IMPECCABLY PUT TOGETHER
column7: I was a bit apprehensive at first because this is basically a documentary work and not a fictional novel. Typically such novels turn out to be boring, void of any suspense. But this one is an exception. From 1st page to last this novel packs in tons and tons of research work so well put together that it is ALMOST a page turner. Almost because some chapters might feel vague and disconnected. But you will soon get over and one thing for sure that after reading this book you will learn that history has been altered to an unimaginable way.
Please buy other editions. This particular edition has tiny font, no line space, and is difficult for your eyes. Its not worth its price

Bear in mind that this review is for the 150th anniversary edition published by Signet Classics. A true modern gem - exquisitely detailed, accurate and methodical. The flow of the book, though a bit tedious at times, never loses its focus. Though I'm not really a fan of paperback books, this particular edition suffices. The only notable drawback is the beige cover which runs the risk of magnifying the smallest of stains. The main highlight of the anniversary edition that differentiates it from others is a stunning introduction by the renowned biologist, Sir Julian Huxley which does a marvelous job of setting the tone of the book and prepares the reader for things to come. Also an efficient historical sketch is provided for refernce. All in all, a top-of-the-line bargain.

column6: A Must Read for any Average Person
column7:
This is the book which talks about how to organize ourselves with the help of Post-it Notes.
It illustrates a methodical understanding of various techniques of problem solving in the most simplistic way, so that anybody can easily understand.
The tools, as the author calls them, are the problem-solving techniques are existing problem-solving methods.
But this made-easy book comes out like a hand-book for simple ways of problem-solving, with simple names for tools in a most easy-to-understand and the most effective way with the sole objective of making us use these techniques in our daily life.
The book explains what's a problem; what's a piece of information; how to arrange it and organize it with charts and illustrations.

I have a three year old Dell Inspiron Laptop, and it gets hot pretty easily, even without running resource heavy applications, So naturally i was in the market for a good cooler, and I simply had two considerations, 

1. Decent cooling 
2. Comfortable on the lap.

I prefer to use my laptop on my lap and there aren't many decent cooling pads in this range that sits comfortably on your lap. I am absolutely happy with the product.

Pros.

Comfortable on the Lap.
Effective cooling with no noise. ( I had to check to see whether it's running, it's that silent.  )
 It's very slim and lightweight.

Cons.

If your laptop doesn't have proper rubber bushing underneath, then it may slide down if you are not careful. In my case, dell provides excellent bushes, so it was not a worry.

P.S It's best suited for a 14 - 15 inch laptop. So keep that in consideration.

Product is somewhat accurate in measuring weight, measures upto 1/10th of a kg, but the fat and water percentage measurements are bullshit. They just take your height and weight into account, and randomly calculates the usual fat, muscle and bone percentage for that. You can do this calculation by yourself with the help of various methods you can find online. Every person's weight varies 1-2 kgs day to day depending on many different factors. But that does NOT mean that the fat percentage has increased or decreased 2% in one day, and that's what this machine shows. And about the measurement of weight, any ordinary weight machine can do that.

I recently brought a dlna enabled wireless Panasonic TV. And had a bsnl type2 teracom wifi modem. Streaming from minidlna wired server, to the tv, was fine. But when i started streaming from the my android phones/tabs the performance was pathetic. May be this was due to too many wireless devices clogging the 2.4Ghz band. So i did some research and ended up with this product. 

Decided to use the bsnl as modem/dhcp server. And configured this router in bypass mode(i might change this setting later). Our laptop/adroid devices/TV are all hooked up in 5Ghz band, with 300Mbps available between them. And zero interference from any neighbor's router, which are all running in 2.4Band. 

In this config when I stream youtube video from android devices, and its getting rendered on TV with out any glitch. All streaming in HD(720p). 

I have no idea about the range of this router. It works well with in 4 rooms that are serially connected. And 2.4 band has more range than 5Ghz band.

If you don't have too many wireless devices and not much interference from the neighbors, then a N300 single band wireless router might be suffice. And you can get that in 1/2 the price. Please do your own research before getting one. Also check out the current routers performance, interference etc using \inSSIDer\" utility."

This tab is the best you can get under 15K for any 10 inch tab.
It has a smooth operation. It has a very good display. And to seamlessly exchange data offline, it has a micro USB cable as accessory . It can also connect to a PC through OTG cable and is good in catching wi-fi signals.

There is a minor drawback, that while playing mkv files the movie stuck at times. I know the mkv file was fine. i tried different players but the problem persisted. It may be that in certain frames a lot of computation goes in mkv video stream decompression, so there the processor may act sluggish.
